About the problem: Given the exponential growth model, y = a b^x, determine parameters a and b provided with two points on the curve.

A graphing tool is provided to help with visualizing the geometry of the problem.
Fully-worked solution is provided.

*************************************************************--> 
<problem>
<setup>
  <selectFromSequence name="m" from="5" to="20"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="n" from="2" to="6"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="p" from="3" to="6"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="q" from="4" to="10"/>
  <math name="p2x" simplify>$p + $q</math>
  <math name="p2y" simplify>$m $n</math>
  <math name="b">$n^(1/$q)</math>
  <math name="a">$m/($b^$p)</math>
  <number name="aN" displayDecimals="7">$a</number>
  <number name="bN" displayDecimals="7">$b</number>
  <point name="p1" fixed>($p, $m)</point>
  <math name="p2m" simplify>($p2x, $p2y)</math>
</setup>


