            Graphing Tool
**********************************************-->

<aside><title>Graphing tool</title>

<setup>
  <number name="xmin">-5</number>
  <number name="xmax">$p2x + 10</number>
  <number name="ymin">-5</number>
  <number name="ymax">$p2y + 10</number>
</setup>
  
<p>Enter given points</p>
<p><m>P_1 = </m> <mathInput name="graphP1"/>, <m>P_2 = </m> <mathInput name="graphP2"/></p>

<p>Enter an approximation for <m>a</m> and <m>b</m> in the equation <m>y = a b^x</m>, or check the answers you obtained algebraically. Values are prefilled initially to give a suggestion of the shape of a simillar growth curve.</p>
<p><m>a = </m><mathInput name="graphA" prefill="1" displayDecimals="3"/>, <m>b = </m><mathInput name="graphB" prefill="2" displayDecimals="3"/></p>

  
<graph name="g1" xmin="$xmin" xmax="$xmax" ymin="$ymin" ymax="$ymax">
  <function name="graphExpFunc" styleNumber="5">$graphA $graphB^x
  </function>
  <label anchor="($p2x, $p2y/2)" positionFromAnchor="right"><math displayDecimals="3">y = $graphExpFunc.formula</math></label>

  <point name="p1g" coords="$graphP1"/>
  <point name="p2g" coords="$graphP2"/>
</graph>

</aside>  



  
<p><m>y = </m> <mathInput name="userA" prefill="a"/> <mathInput name="userB" prefill="b"/><m>^x</m></p>
  <answer name="ans1">
    <award name="correct" allowedErrorInNumbers="0.001" allowedErrorIsAbsolute>
      <when>$userA = $a and $userB = $b</when>
    </award>
    <award  name="rounding" credit="0.5" allowedErrorInNumbers="0.01" allowedErrorIsAbsolute>
      <when>$userA = $a and $userB = $b</when>
    </award>
  </answer>
<p>You've entered <m>y = $userA \cdot $userB^x</m></p>



